SubmitterDescription.SubmitterName: International Standards For Cytogenomic Arrays Consortium (ISCA)

SampleDescription.Description: mosaic: FISH - 12.5% of interphase nuclei from a PHA-stimulated culture as well as 12.0% of interphase nuclei from a direct preparation. A limited chromosome study focusing on chromosome 9 confirmed that of 50 metaphases, 1 was trisomy 9 and the remaining 49 metaphases had two normal chromosomes 9 and an additional copy of chromosome 9 containing the entire p-arm, centromere, and only the qh region of the q-arm. Therefore, the net result is duplication of 9pter to 9q12 in the majority of cells, and whole chromosome trisomy 9 in a small percentage of cells. Phenotype: IUGR, positional abnormality of the left foot, low-set ears, clinodactyly, palmar crease, heart murmur, prematurity
